				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">AoE Kiting?<a name="25012"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 2 04 2:28 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hey all!
<br />

<br />
First off, been reading the boards for quite awhile now, first time posting. Wanted to say what a great buncha people we have here, as fun as it is to be a bard, it's even cooler to have a player community that is as genuinely nice as I've met here. (not that there aren't bards that are jerks, they just don't seem to be here) <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
Anyway, to my first question. I'm currently level 41, reasonably equipped and have been xp'ing off the darkpaw knolls in JP forest. Either groupping or chant kiting have been my methods so far. I'm also able to take some of them on brute force alone. My question comes in as I've read about people talking about AoE kiting. I'm curious as to how this is done?
<br />

<br />
Our AoE's are PB AoE's from what I've seen so far and I've used them in my regular group setups when I was pure DPS. Originally CoD, then CoD and DDD, finally DDD and Fufils (which I realize is not an AoE). 
<br />

<br />
So, for AoE kiting do you actually have to stop to let the mobs catch up with you as you trigger the AoE's? This seems like it would be exceptionally difficult and I can't imagine even possible with large sized kites.
<br />

<br />
Also thought I would share a little tip that I've been using lately. I'm regularly the puller for groups I'm in and of course am always pulling when I'm soloing/duoing. I've rotated the spells I've used to pull depending on the situation. I used to pull with snare if I wanted to manuver/chant the mob during the pull, and just Fufils if I was straight pulling to the group. One trick I found was when splitting a pair in an outdoor situation I would just have selos up, snare one and haul bard buns back to the group. The unsnared one would more or less keep up but the snared one would fall far enough behind to lose aggro getting me a nice single pull.
<br />

<br />
The other trick was I was always having issues with buffed mobs particularly sow / hastened ones. Well, when I hit 40 instead of using fufils for pulls I already knew would be single pulls I started using Syvelians. It has been working great!
<br />

<br />
Anyway, if anyone could enlighten me on the AoE kiting issue I would love to hear about it!
<br />

<br />
Thanks!
<br />

<br />
-Ampd</span></td>
