			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AoE Kiting?<a name="25028"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 2 04 3:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>AoE Kiting does take a bit of pratice to get it right, but once you get it going it is great <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />. here is what i have done in my 20's in HSM on the Sonic Wolves and Owlbears. i would suggest you pratice here first for it will give you pratice, no exp at your level but great pratice.
<br />

<br />
first equip a horn, no drum needed for our sung Selo is faster than their run speed. run along the island close to Pad Caverns, not the south islands yet.
<br />

<br />
gather up a few wolves or owlbears, four or five to start, then head back to a nice flat area.
<br />

<br />
now start running in a few circles (i usually do more of an oval type run). singing Selo and DDD. if you do not get the message that your targets are affected. then run a little closer together. You will see that the area that the song effects is larger than you think.
<br />

<br />
once in a while you will get taged by them, dont worry that happens, just run a larger circle singing heal and you will be ok. I currently have the Iksar Chestplate so i never worry about that much.
<br />

<br />
Once you have done this a few times and are felling the power that AoE offers starting pulling the south islands. BUT only when it is overran by Owlbears. these do not cast root (bards worst enemy). And remember we are still just praticing our skill on this. 
<br />

<br />
Once you start pulling the islands you will have a good size train following you, about 30-40   <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-3.gif" border="0" alt="Scared" hspace="2" />  this is good to show you the real power of AoE. 
<br />

<br />
Now that you have done this, you will slap your self for not tring this sooner, i know, for i have slaped my self on this.
<br />

<br />
What i will tell you is this is a great way to raise in levels, for at LvL 25 i got about 40-50% on my exp bar doing these type of trains in about 10 minutes. Yea that much. but i have a lot of training to do on my other skills such as ATK and DEF.
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps, 
<br />
Mampas</span></td>
