				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AoE Kiting?<a name="25075"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 2 04 5:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>AOE Denons and horn worked big numbers for me... I started experimenting in LOIO with Sarnak fort. Pulling 4 or so at a time. By the time it was light blue to me, I was pulling upwards to 15 sarnaks at a time. Beasties that can not keep pace with me suffer a terrible rathe. I was pulling from skel tower to the gob hut for 12 or so creatures (kill group 1)and then hitting the fort (kill group 2). By the time I was done with the sarnak masses the skels and gobs had respawned. As long as there are no casters and the creature is blown back by Denons its fine. There are times when the mob will catch you and you can watch yourself go down<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />but the xp gained back in the 9 trains you do pull outweigh the xp loss of one.
<br />
Currently I am running circles on Ice Clad Port In isle. I am grabbing groups of 12+ dire wolves. Just pull them to the flats back towards zone bridge to left. It does take 20 mins or so to take down the pack but again xp is unmatched by anything else. I have tried the spirocs (more loot at spirocs) but was not as impressed. I have gone from 38-43 in no time. One train of wolves is totaling 16% gain in yellow bar per train.
<br />
Time off now to rework some group twisting and melle skills.... xp is soooo slow<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />
Will try and add more as I find them.
