			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: AoE Kiting?<a name="26708"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 11:40 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>You must have run3 to kite indoors without getting hit.  While doing this you can't make small circles like you do when you are outdoors.  You must time your turns with your casting.  I usually make a small box when kiting indoors.  I pretty much make 2-3 90 degree turns during a single song cast.  Outdoors it is much simpler.  I just cast Selo's and gather the mobs.  Then I make a couple medium sized circles to get them all nice and tight.  Once tight I start to make smaller circles until I feel that I am ready to engage.  When I engage (I have auto run on the entire time) I make a sharp turn by holding down the turn button.  Do not let go of the turn button unless you are running for the zone or get hit.  While holding down the turn buttong you will notice that you aren't running a circle, but are running in more of an elipse pattern.  To adjust your movement, just change your camera angle.  You can not do the tight circles from the first person view.  You will turn too sharply and end up right in the middle of your mobs.  AoE kiting is tricky business.  You will die a lot at first.  Once you get used to it, the deaths will be less frequent.  If you don't like to die, stick with grouping and slow exp.  If you like/want fast exp, try AoE kiting.  There's no greater feeling than taking out 40 mobs in 30 min.  Yes, 30 min is a long time to kite, but when you kill 40 mobs in this amount of time that's less than 1 min per mob.  Most groups take about 2 min to kill a single mob. =)  Good luck, and enjoy.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
