				<td colspan="2"><span>I really don't get that &quot;AoE is exciting&quot;.  I like to finish off a level with AoE but that running in circles is the most mind numbing thing that a bard can do.  I really don't buy &quot;running a macro and taking a nap&quot;.  That's a good way to wake up to a wipe and a bunch of angry groupmates.  
<br />

<br />
Reality check,  lets suppose the group of mobs you've rounded up are all worth 1% of a level.  20 make a yellow bubble but there's a chance that after you make the next level some of those are going to go green on you.  You may start kiting in an area and get half a level in one kite but it won't take too many levels till that just peters out.  Of course there are the deaths and mobs warping off to the zone line.  
<br />

<br />
As I said,  I AoE but it's my absolute least favorite thing to do.  I mean there's nothing like kiting 30+ mobs and getting 5% of a level.  What a drag <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /></span></td>
